edu.stanford.nlp.ling

Class TaggedWord

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.stanford.nlp.ling.ValueLabel
      • edu.stanford.nlp.ling.StringLabel
        • edu.stanford.nlp.ling.Word
          • edu.stanford.nlp.ling.TaggedWord
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HasOffset, HasTag, HasWord, Label, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ValueLabel>

    public class TaggedWord
extends Word
implements HasTag
    A TaggedWord object contains a word and its tag. The value() of a TaggedWord is the Word. The tag is secondary.
    Author:
    Christopher Manning
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • setFromString

        public void setFromString(java.lang.String taggedWord)
        Sets a TaggedWord from decoding the String passed in. The String is divided according to the divider character (usually, "/"). We assume that we can always just divide on the rightmost divider character, rather than trying to parse up escape sequences. If the divider character isn't found in the word, then the whole string becomes the word, and the tag is null.
        Specified by:
        setFromString in interface Label
        Overrides:
        setFromString in class StringLabel
        Parameters:
        taggedWord - The word that will go into the Word
